    • Method Detail

      • computeSuccessors

        Collection<ProgramState> computeSuccessors(ProgramState programState)
                                    throws NotSufficientlyMaterializedException,
                                           StateSpaceGenerationAbortedException
        Executes a single step of the abstract program semantics on the given program state. Since the abstract program semantics may be non-deterministic (for example if a conditional statement cannot be evaluated), this results in a set of successor program states in general.
        Parameters:
        programState - The state on which the abstract program semantics shall be executed.
        Returns:
        All states resulting from executing the program semantics on programState.
        Throws:
        NotSufficientlyMaterializedException - This exception is thrown if the semantics cannot be executed on programState due to missing fields.
        StateSpaceGenerationAbortedException

      • getPotentialViolationPoints

        ViolationPoints getPotentialViolationPoints()
        Returns:
        All potential violation points that may prevent execution of this statement.

      • getSuccessorPCs

        Set<Integer> getSuccessorPCs()
        Returns:
        The set of all program locations that are direct successors of this program statement in the underlying control flow graph.

      • needsCanonicalization

        boolean needsCanonicalization()
        Returns:
        true, if the statement always requires canonicalization
